explanation: The solution works by shifting both the left and right boundaries to the right until they become equal. The number of shifts required to make them equal is the number of bits that are different between the two numbers. The result is then obtained by shifting the common prefix back to the left by the same number of bits. This approach takes advantage of the properties of bitwise operations and binary representation of numbers.

